----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Container vs. Bean managed transactions
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--- Container Managed Transactions (CMT) ---
manage transactions declaratively

--- Bean Managed Transactions (BMT) ---
manage transactions programmatically

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Transaction Management
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--- Local vs. Global Transactions ---
- local transactions: 1 resource
- global transactions: >1 resources

--- Declarative Transaction Management ---
with xml configuration or annotations

--- Programmatic Transaction Management ---
- not used very often
- springs TransactionTemplate class gives full control over the
  transaction management code

--- Global Transactions with JTA ---
- transactions that span multiple backend resources
- 2 Phase commit ensures, that all backend resources were updated or rolled back together
